4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the untimely passing of
6 Tre'Shun McGee; and
7 WHEREAS, Tre'Shun was born on January 19, 2012, in Monroe, Louisiana, to
8 Danielle Jones and Travis McGee; he was an intelligent, kind, and energetic young man who
9 made an impact on all who knew him; and
10 WHEREAS, Tre'Shun was known for his smile, loving personality, and goofiness;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, Tre'Shun attended Martin Luther King Jr. Junior High School, where
13 he played basketball, ran track, and was a member of the school band; he was a bright
14 student and member of the Beta Club, where he served in the role of historian; and
15 WHEREAS, Tre'Shun loved sports and playing video games, especially Fortnite and
16 2K; and
17 WHEREAS, Tre'Shun McGee leaves to cherish his memory three dedicated sisters,
18 Makaela, Kaeyln, and Shontasia; four other sisters; four brothers; maternal grandmother,
19 Carrie Jones; maternal grandfather, Gregory Owens; paternal grandmother, Pamela McGee;
20 paternal grandfather, Matthew Cooper; favorite aunt, Stormye Jones; two favorite uncles,
21 Christopher Jones and Damion Jones; and a host of cousins and extended relatives; he will
